Great, you're all set up to use a Chef server. With your cookbook uploaded to the Chef server, you're now ready to scale-out your infrastructure!

The next step is to set up a second server to configure and run the cookbook on it. In [Learn the basics](/learn-the-basics/ubuntu/), you ran `chef-apply` and `chef-client` to configure your server directly. Now you'll use `knife` to configure your server remotely from your workstation.
